      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt the chocolate and mix the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 170°C fan. Grease and line a 20 cm round cake tin. Melt the {{dark-chocolate}} and {{unsalted-butter}} together using a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "bain-marie",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp1gmolt00030sv4n3xzzjhh"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", stirring until smooth. Remove from the heat and stir in 100 g of the {{caster-sugar}}, the egg yolks, {{vanilla-extract}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}}. Fold in the {{almond-flour}} and {{cocoa-powder}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fold in the egg whites and bake, 28 to 32 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "In a clean bowl, beat the egg whites with a hand mixer until soft peaks form. Add the remaining 50 g of {{caster-sugar}} and continue beating until firm, glossy peaks hold. Fold one-third of the egg whites into the chocolate mixture to loosen it, then fold in the remaining two-thirds in two additions, cutting through the batter rather than stirring, until just combined. Pour into the prepared tin and bake for 28 to 32 minutes. The edges should be set and the centre should have a slight wobble. Cool in the tin for 30 minutes before turning out. Dust with {{icing-sugar}} to serve.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
